fields.name: Apple Cider Vinegar
fields.description: Apple Cider Vinegar can be used in sauces, pickles or marinades as well as salad dressings mixed with olive or flaxseed oil. Our Organic Apple Cider Vinegar has all the raw enzymes or 'The Mother' included and is mild due to its low acidity. It can also be used as a key ingredients to making a vegan cheese dip.
fields.ingredients: Organic Raw Apple Cider Vinegar (5% acidity)

fields.name: Baking Powder
fields.description: This non-organic baking powder is a classic raising agent for adding to plain flour when making cakes, scones and puddings.
fields.ingredients: Mono Calcium Phosphate, Corn Starch, Sodium Bicarbonate.

fields.name: Aduki Beans
fields.description: Organic Aduki Beans are a great addition to any food lover's kitchen. Use their sweet and nutty umami goodness to make top-notch stews, soups and savoury dishes. But adukis will also serve you well in creating satisfying desserts as well as Japanese, Chinese and other Far Eastern classics like dim sum.

fields.name: Black Eyed Beans
fields.description: Black eyed beans are a fibre-rich protein source that is extremely versatile and popular in vegan and vegetarian diets. Delicious added to stews and hearty meals such as vegan shepherd's pie for added texture and protein.

fields.name: Black Turtle Beans
fields.description: Organic black turtle beans, also known as just black beans, are rich in fibre and protein and are a popular ingredient in Latin American cuisine. They have a dense, meaty texture that adds substance to vegetarian dishes such as stews making them popular with vegans as a reliable protein source.

fields.name: Butter Beans
fields.description: Organic butter beans , also known as lima beans, have a deliciously subtle buttery flavour and a soft, smooth texture. They are often used in baking sweet treats for their moisture and the texture it can add to a bake. Try making butter bean dip instead of hummus or add to stews for added protein.

fields.name: Calypso Beans
fields.description: Organic Calypso Beans are a lesser-known yet visually impressive and utterly delicious umami cooking ingredient. Pick some up to make formidable stews, soups, casseroles, vegetarian chili dishes, tomato-based savoury meals and much more.

fields.name: Cannellini Beans
fields.description: Organic cannellini beans are popularly used in Italy for dishes such as minestrone. They are medium-sized white kidney beans and can take the place of butter beans in recipes such as stews, hotpot and soups.

fields.name: Mung Beans
fields.description: Our organic mung beans are completely natural and organic and once cooked can be enjoyed hot or cold. Mung beans are one of the best sources of vegan protein and essential amino acids. Many people enjoy mung beans as part of a healthy, balanced diet to contribute to reducing health problems.

fields.name: Pinto Beans
fields.description: Incredibly similar to Borlotti Beans, these organic pinto beans are great for adding to recipes such as soups, stews, homemade beans on toast, tasty dips and countless more recipes from across Europe and far beyond!

fields.name: Red Kidney Beans
fields.description: Kidney beans are given the name due to their resemblance to the human kidney in shape and colour. They are high in protein and fibre and provide an abundance of nutrients to a meal of your choosing.

fields.name: Soya Beans
fields.description: Soya beans are vegan friendly and can be used in many ways as a vegan protein source in recipes in the same way as chickpeas. Belonging to the legume family, the soya bean which has been important in oriental cuisine for a number of years, and the soya beans only got introduced to the western world recently where it has become more of an important protein source for vegans and vegetarians.

fields.name: Black Rice
fields.description: Organic Black Rice is an excellent accompaniment to several dishes from several cuisines. Black rice is similar to brown rice and is rich in fibre and protein. The dark colour means that it is packed full of vitamins and nutrients including anthocyanins. Anthocyanins are present in rich coloured foods such as black rice, raspberries, blueberries and purple broccoli.

fields.name: Dry Chickpeas
fields.description: Organic Chickpeas add protein, fibre and a vibrant mix of vitamins and minerals to all kinds of recipes, they are great in curries and are the main ingredient for making hummus. Because of its incredible versatility, you can use these organic chickpeas such as, roasting them with warming spices and enjoying them as a go-to healthy snack. You can also use it to make curries like chana masala, an Indian side dish that is popular with vegans.

fields.name: Cornflakes
fields.description: Made from 100% organic corn, our cornflakes are loaded with essential nutrients and vitamins. Mainly used at breakfast time, these cornflakes are also used a lot in making corn flake cakes or you can make a tasty cereal bar.

fields.name: Organic Mango Pieces (Sweet)
fields.description: These Organic Mango Pieces have a deliciously sweet taste, this product is also known as the Brooks variety, they have a pale colour and sweet flavour with a soft bite. When it is naturally dried, the mango's natural colour and shape is preserved and it also goes to a chewy texture which is a satisfying thing to sink your teeth into.

fields.name: Dried Apple Rings
fields.description: These chewy, succulent and super-sweet apple rings are a perfect snack, and a wonderful baking fodder too. Use them to make handy fruit and nut snacks, classic apple pies and other tangy, fruity desserts. Add spices like vanilla, ginger, cinnamon and cardamom to your apple rings, and soak, bake, or even batter them! Extra-delicious with ice cream.

fields.name: Dried Apricots
fields.description: Dried apricots are highly nutritious and a great source of natural fruit fibre. Enjoy as a snack or dice up and add to baking and cooking such as Moroccan cuisine. Because of its versatility, these dried apricots are perfect for adding to a number of recipes like porridges, curries, jams and so many more sweet and savoury recipes.

fields.name: Dried Sweet Cherries
fields.description: This top-quality foodstuff will help you make world-beating porridge, fruit crumbles and countless other sweet treats. It's also great when added to muesli and other cereals too.

fields.name: Dried Figs
fields.description: Organic dried figs are naturally sweet and juicy and great for snacking on. They are rich in vitamins and minerals and high in soluble fibre, which can be great for a healthy digestive system. Fresh figs are delicately soft and fruity and great paired with cheese and used to make chutneys.

fields.name: Peach Halves Dried
fields.description: Discover the delightful taste of our premium Dried Peach Halves, a healthy and convenient snack that captures the essence of summer all year round. These succulent treats offer a burst of natural sweetness and a chewy texture that can be enjoyed on their own or added to various dishes.

fields.name: Dried Pears
fields.description: These top-notch unsweetened pear halves will embue your porridge, cereals, puddings, desserts, and a sweet snack with superb natural tang and sweetness. Pick some up to impress your taste buds, friends, family, and guests.

fields.name: Pitted Deglet Noir Dates
fields.description: Deglet Nour dates can be enjoyed as a sweet snack to satisfy those cravings and can be used as a natural sweetener in various different baking recipes. They are sweet, juicy and have a dreamy caramel texture and flavour.

fields.name: Dried Cranberries
fields.description: Our dried cranberries are sweetened with sugar giving it a more enjoyable flavour than fresh cranberries, which can have a slightly bitter taste. Great added to home baking in muffins, biscuits, cakes and bread. Buy cranberries to sprinkle on top of your morning oats for a subtly sweet, warming and nutritious breakfast.

fields.name: Goji Berries
fields.description: Goji berries can be enjoyed as a snack or added to baking or even topping your breakfast bowl - they work great on smoothie bowls along with your favourite nuts, seeds, and a dollop of coconut yoghurt.

fields.name: Pitted Prunes
fields.description: Dried pitted prunes are a great source of dietary fibre and a delicious go-to snack throughout the day. There are a number of health benefits associated with consuming prunes such as improving digestion and providing energy. Although high in natural sugars, do not cause blood sugar levels to spike, which prevents dips in energy.
fields.ingredients: chilean ashlock pitted prunes, sunflower oil, potassium sorbate (E202)

fields.name: Thompson Raisins
fields.description: Known for their naturally sweet taste and plump texture, these sun-dried grapes offer a rich, fruity flavour that can enhance a wide variety of dishes. Whether you are baking bread, adding a touch of sweetness to a salad, or simply enjoying them as a healthy snack, Thompson Raisins provide the perfect burst of natural sweetness.

fields.name: Brown Rice Flour
fields.description: This top-quality organic brown rice flour is stoneground to make it extra-fine and absolutely unbeatable as a versatile cooking ingredient. Rice flour is a fantastic culinary asset to own: use it to make magical crackers, noodles, pancakes, dumplings, homemade bread and much more. It's also a great thickening agent and works well in soups, gravies, stuffings, sauces and stews.

fields.name: Defatted Almond Flour
fields.description: Ideal for baking and cooking alike, it's a fantastic low-carb and gluten-free alternative to traditional wheat flour. Whether you're whipping up a batch of fluffy pancakes or crafting a crust for your favourite pie, our flour is your ally for delectable creations with a healthier twist.
fields.ingredients: Almond flour from part-oiled, blanched, sweet almonds

fields.name: Gluten-Free Plain White Flour (Doves Farm)
fields.description: This special flour blend is milled from gluten free ingredients is a great alternative to everyday wheat flour. Follow a gluten free recipe or adapt a traditional recipe by adding a little extra liquid.
fields.ingredients: Flour blend (rice, potato, tapioca, maize, buckwheat)

fields.name: Gluten-Free Self-Raising White Flour (Doves Farm)
fields.description: Award-winning gluten free self raising flour blend from Doves Farm. A blend of naturally gluten free ingredients, use this flour as an alternative to self raising flour made from wheat.
fields.ingredients: Flour blend (rice, potato, tapioca, maize & buckwheat), raising agents (mono-calcium phosphate, sodium bicarbonate), thickener (xanthan gum).

fields.name: Semolina (Fine)
fields.description: One of the world's most versatile ingredients, semolina is loved universally not only for its flavour and nutritional value but for its durability.It's coarsely ground from durum wheat and will serve you well in making traditional pasta, gnocchi, bread, pizza bases and semolina pudding.

fields.name: Plain White Flour
fields.description: Plain white flour is one of those classic, quintessential cooking and baking ingredients. It's been used throughout the UK and Europe for centuries. And thanks to it's versatility, wonderful texture and very useful physical properties, this is likely to remain the case for centuries.
fields.ingredients: organic flour (organic WHEAT flour, calcium, iron, niacin, thiamin)

fields.name: Whole Wheat Flour
fields.description: It is created by grinding wheat in its whole form for all of the natural goodness of the full grain. The finished product is a healthy whole grain that makes the perfect bread and other creations. Wholemeal flour will require you to knead the dough for longer to build up elasticity.

fields.name: Freeze-Dried Blackcurrants
fields.description: Introducing our premium Freeze Dried Whole Blackcurrants, a must-have superfood to elevate your daily diet. Bursting with an intense, tart flavour that perfectly balances sweet and sour notes, these blackcurrants are a delicious way to infuse your meals with a vibrant taste and a nutritional punch.

fields.name: Freeze-Dried Blueberry Powder
fields.description: Experience the incredible power of blueberries in your own kitchen with our exceptional 100% Pure Freeze Dried Blueberry Powder! Bursting with natural antioxidants, our blueberry powder is a must-have addition to your daily diet.

fields.name: Freeze-Dried Dragon Fruit
fields.description: Each slice offers a tantalisingly sweet and slightly tangy flavour, capturing the essence of tropical bliss in every bite. Our dragon fruit slices are not only a delightful snack on their own but also a versatile ingredient that can enhance the visual appeal and taste of your meals.

fields.name: Freeze-Dried Raspberries
fields.description: Freeze dried raspberries have a deliciously sweet flavour and a light and airy feel. Great for snacking on or topping your favourite breakfast or rehydrate to use in baking muffins, cakes and biscuits. Available in bulk sizes for keen bakers and businesses.

fields.name: Freeze-Dried Sour Cherry
fields.description: Perfectly preserved at the peak of their ripeness, these sour cherries retain all their natural tartness and nutritional goodness. Whether you're looking to add a zesty kick to your morning cereal, elevate your baking recipes, or simply enjoy a healthy snack straight from the bag, our Freeze Dried Sour Cherries are the versatile ingredient your pantry has been missing.

fields.name: Freeze-Dried Acai Berry Powder
fields.description: Acai berries are high in nutrients, amino acids and vitamins which make them a great food for energy. The Acai berry powder can be mixed into smoothies and drinks for an easy way to boost your daily nutrients. The high amount of fibre present in the berries could also make them great for a healthy bowel function.

fields.name: Acerola Cherry Powder
fields.description: Acerola Cherry Powder, also known as Barbados or West Indian Cherries, are native to South, and Central America, and are known as being one of the richest natural sources of vitamin C. Acerola cherries are often harvested while still green, as this is when the vitamin C content is at its highest.

fields.name: Banana Powder
fields.description: Banana powder is a fantastic product, which you need in your cupboards. This versatile powder is fantastic to add to smoothies, porridge or baking for extra vitamins and minerals.

fields.name: Raspberry Powder
fields.description: Organic Raspberry Fruit Powder is long-lasting and very tasty. It's also a great way to ensure a regular supply of this classic and completely unique flavour. Blend it into smoothies, shakes and fresh juices for added nutrition and flavourful 'oomph'.

fields.name: Garlic Granules
fields.description: Dried garlic granules have so many uses in the kitchen. Use them to fry or bake vegetables, mushrooms and other foods, or let their flavour infuse your tomato-based dishes, curries, soups and other hot sauces. Alternatively, create a simple flavourful garnish by mixing them with a high-quality seasoning (such as Himalayan salt), ready to grind over all your favourite meals.

fields.name: Black Quinoa
fields.description: Black quinoa is a crunchier and more flavorful counterpart of white quinoa but still as useful and versatile. It's packed with protein and plenty of nutritious goodness, and you can use it not only in place of rice, lentils, pulses, pasta and other umami foods - but also to make many great sweet vegan recipes.

fields.name: Buckwheat
fields.description: Despite its name, raw organic buckwheat is not actually wheat at all. It can be enjoyed in place of other grains such as rice, couscous or quinoa. And it can also be used as porridge and topped with your favourite sweet and healthy toppings such as fresh or dried fruit, nuts and seeds.

fields.name: White Couscous
fields.description: Organic white couscous is slightly sweeter and less earthy than its wholewheat counterpart. It's the perfect ally for making French, Spanish, Italian and Mediterranean meals, tomato-sauces, creamy dishes, salads, fried vegetables and many an exotic dish.

fields.name: Giant White Couscous
fields.description: Giant white couscous is a classic grain which is puffy and delightfully stodgy. Use its matchless umami flavour to make exceptional salads, Mediterranean dishes, soups, vegetable medleys and a whole host of other tasty wholesome recipes.

fields.name: Kamut Grain
fields.description: Kamut Grain is a fantastic wheat product which has a smooth texture and a taste that is both nutty and buttery. It is a great addition to stews, and salads and can be used as an alternative to rice in several dishes.

fields.name: Popping Corn
fields.description: A snacking favourite across the UK, Europe and far beyond. You really cannot beat popping your very own popcorn in the oven or microwave. This tip-top popcorn has both an irresistable brittle-soft crunch and a very versatile flavour. Perfect for both super-sweet and salty-savoury vegan and lower-GI popcorn recipes.

fields.name: Red Quinoa
fields.description: Red quinoa is a rare grain and has a mild, sweet fluffy texture. It is also the crunchier and more flavorful counterpart of white quinoa but is still as useful and versatile. Not only a perfect rice and couscous alternative but quinoa can also be added to salads, stir-fries and try replacing your morning oats with quinoa for a fluffy alternative to porridge.

fields.name: Spelt Grain
fields.description: Spelt is a type of wheat that was widely grown in Roman times and is now widely introduced into baking across the world, it is widely used because of its high protein content. The whole grain can be used as a substitute for risotto rice and can be ground into flour at home if required.

fields.name: Brown Basmati Rice
fields.description: Organic basmati brown rice includes the bran and germ, meaning it contains much more fibre content than white basmati rice that has these removed. Basmati rice is a unique grain, it expands more than twice its length when it is cooking, also unlike other rice, it expands lengthways.

fields.name: Buckwheat Flakes
fields.description: Buckwheat flakes are a great breakfast ingredient and have a delicious, mild and almost nutty flavour. Use to make porridge, muesli and even breakfast muffins to start the day right.

fields.name: Bulgur Wheat
fields.description: Bulgur wheat is created by milling the wheat berries into smaller pieces, this process will give your cooking an advantage by reducing the cooking time while retaining all the nutritious goodness of whole bulgur wheat.

fields.name: Hulled Millet
fields.description: Organic hulled millet is a versatile small grain that can be used in place of couscous or rice at mealtimes. Millet needs to be hulled before human consumption as the grain is naturally hard and indigestible.

fields.name: Jumbo Oats
fields.description: These oats can enhance several recipes in a number of different recipes, such as it pairs well with all fresh and dried fruit, nuts and seeds and even chocolate, and they can be made into overnight oats for a quick and easy healthy breakfast.

fields.name: Oat Groats
fields.description: Oat groats are the hulled kernels of oats and have had minimal processing. Groats are a whole grain and include the fibre-rich part of the grain and retain the endosperm. This is what your traditional porridge oats look like before they are milled and rolled to make flakes.

fields.name: Porridge Oats
fields.description: Oats can be enjoyed at any time of day for a healthy meal that is good for the body. It is a slow-release energy food that keeps you satisfied and fuller for longer whilst feeling full of energy ready to take on anything.

fields.name: White Quinoa
fields.description: Organic quinoa is a fantastic grain that is rich in protein and high in fibre making it the perfect ingredient for anyone on a vegan diet. It is the perfect alternative to rice or couscous and does not have any gluten-containing ingredients.

fields.name: Rye Grain
fields.description: Discover the rich, hearty flavour of our Organic Rye Grain. Known for its robust and slightly nutty taste, this grain is a versatile addition to your pantry, perfect for a variety of culinary applications.

fields.name: Tricolour Quinoa
fields.description: Our Organic Quinoa Grain (Tricolour) is a combination of 70% White, 15% Red and 15% Black Quinoa. Quinoa is versatile, quick-cooking and very nutritious. It is often used by people on gluten-free diets. It is incredibly popular as it adds a pop of colour to meals such as salads and stir-fries.
fields.ingredients: Organic Quinoa Grain Tricolour 15% Red, 15% Black, 70% White

fields.name: Granola
fields.description: The best granola comes in the smallest sizes and this granola is small in size but packs a massive flavour. This cereal is packed with dried fruit and mixed seeds to make it a healthy breakfast for everyone.
fields.ingredients: granola base* (gluten free scottish oat flakes*), coconut sugar*, buckwheat raw*, coconut powder*, linseeds milled*, sultanas*(sunflower oil*), apricots chopped*(rice flour*), coconut chips toasted*. *organic

fields.name: Acacia Honey
fields.description: This Organic Raw Acacia Honey comes from the black locust or false acacia tree. Raw Acacia Bulgarian Honey is a light and clear colour and is both nutritious and mouth-wateringly tasty.

fields.name: Irish Kombu
fields.description: Organic Irish Kombu (Kelp) is a brown seaweed and one of a number of different varieties of kelp found in Irish waters. It is good source of glutamic acid, an amino acid responsible for umami - a delicious, savoury taste.

fields.name: Apricot Jam
fields.description: This nutritious range from FruTeto Italia is simply crushed fruit in a jar. It has been created to replace traditional jam. Made from organic fruit only, without pectin, preservatives or refined sugar. We cook it gently in small batches using hand picked, fully ripe fruit from the orchard.
fields.ingredients: Fruit* (7 apricots*, apple*), grape juice concentrate*, lemon juice*. Contains naturally occurring sugars from fruit only. *Organic

fields.name: Blueberry Jam
fields.description: This nutritious range from FruTeto Italia is crushed fruit in a jar. It has been created to replace traditional jam. Made from organic fruit only, without preservatives or refined sugar. We cook it gently in small batches using hand-picked, fully ripe fruit from the orchard.
fields.ingredients: Fruit* (184 blueberries*) , grape juice concentrate*, lemon juice*, Pectin*, *Organic. Contains naturally occurring sugars from fruit only.

fields.name: Raspberry Jam
fields.description: This nutritious range from FruTeto Italia is simply crushed fruit in a jar. It has been created to replace traditional jam. This raspberry spread is delicious by the spoonful, or on toast or brioche, it can also be swirled into natural yogurt or smoothies. Or used to make desserts like sorbet or jam tarts.
fields.ingredients: Fruit* (130 raspberries*, apple*), grape juice concentrate*, lemon juice*. Contains naturally occurring sugars from fruit only. *Organic

fields.name: Strawberry Jam
fields.description: This strawberry spread is delicious by the spoonful in the dark days of winter or spread on hot toast - why not try it the Italian way without butter? As an alternative to compote, it is perfect for drizzling over desserts.
fields.ingredients: Fruit* (28 strawberries*), grape juice concentrate*, lemon juice* Contains naturally occurring sugars from fruit only. *Organic

fields.name: Lentils (Brown)
fields.description: These organic brown lentils mix excellently with all other pulses, beans, lentils, rice and stodgy food, as well as virtually every savoury spice in existence - and a number of herbs. Grab some of these moreish, heart-warming lentils to make classic Indian dahl dishes, crowd-pleasing soups and many more favour-winning meals.

fields.name: Lentils (Green)
fields.description: These large and very striking green lentils turn green once cooked, they are high in fibre, protein and they are a perfect slow-cooker ingredient, and ideal for stews, broths and casseroles.

fields.name: Lentils (Red)
fields.description: Red lentils are one of the easiest legumes to cook, they are packed with protein, iron and fibre. They are used in various savoury dishes such as curries, soups and dahls.

fields.name: Lentils (Yellow Split)
fields.description: Yellow split lentils add a great colour to dishes and are used in the Indian dish dhal. A protein rich carbohydrate full of fibre and nutrients. Great for sprinkling on salads or adding to a flavour-rich stew and are prepared in the same way as other lentils.

fields.name: Matcha Powder
fields.description: Matcha green tea is one of the finest â€“ if not the finest â€“ tea in the world. This wonderful, hailing from the Far East, is a vibrant green powder is a real wonder food, full of goodness and itâ€™s extremely tasty too.

fields.name: Mixed Nuts (No Peanuts)
fields.description: We believe our mixed nuts to be a flawless standalone snack. It's great for bulking out breakfasts like porridge or cereals and adding to cakes and desserts. Our finest mixture of nuts, we and many of our customers, believe them to be just about as delicious as mixed nuts get.
fields.ingredients: ALMONDS, CASHEWS, HAZELNUTS, WALNUT halves, BRAZILS, PECANS

fields.name: Assorted Muesli
fields.description: This very simple muesli base is delicious and highly nutritious, it is perfect for pairing with any nuts, fruits, seeds, spices and sweet foods.
fields.ingredients: Organic Porridge OATS, Organic Jumbo OATS, Organic WHEAT Flakes, Organic BARLEY Flakes

fields.name: Gluten-Free Muesli
fields.description: Kick start your day with our gluten free fruity oat muesli, a unique blend of real fruits & crunchy seeds. Mix with yoghurt or your choice of milk for a tasty a fulfilling breakfast. This gluten-free muesli is full of fibre, vital nutrients and slow-releasing energy, which ensures you are feeling fuller for longer.
fields.ingredients: OATS gluten free, sultanas (sunflower oil), dates chopped(rice flour), sunflower seeds, linseeds brown, flame raisins (sunflower oil), papaya diced (dehydrated, with sugar & SULPHUR DIOXIDE).

fields.name: Nutritional Yeast Flakes
fields.description: Our nutritional yeast flakes (also known as nooch) are fortified with B12 providing a rich source of vitamins and minerals which is ideal for vegans. Yeast flakes are a natural food grown on fortified beet molasses under carefully controlled conditions.
fields.ingredients: Nutritional Yeast (Saccharomyces cerevisiae, inactive), Vitamin D yeast, cyanocobalamin (B12).

fields.name: Almond Butter
fields.description: Our Organic Raw Almond Butter is made from 100% raw organic almonds and is completely vegan and vegetarian friendly. There has been no heat treatment to our almonds to remove the skins. This increases the fibre content of the almond butter too.

fields.name: Almond Cream
fields.description: Organic dairy-free almond cooking cream, alternative to dairy and soya single creams.
fields.ingredients: Water, almond* (7%), sunflower oil*, agave syrup*, stabiliser (arabic gum*, xanthane gum), emulsifier: sunflower lecithin*, sea salt, natural flavouring*. *organic

fields.name: Almond Flour
fields.description: Almond flour has a sweet, nutty flavour and is an essential baking ingredient amongst avid bakers and is perfect for making cakes, pastries and biscuits. Being Keto, low carb and vegan friendly, this is the perfect flour alternative for those who need to add to their baking repertoire.

fields.name: Almond Milk
fields.description: This drink is 100% vegan-friendly and is perfect to add to coffee or just to drink on its own. With this drink being lactose-free, this is perfect for those with specific dietary requirements.
fields.ingredients: Natural spring water, organic rice (14%), organic italian almonds (1%), organic cold-pressed sunflower oil, sea salt.

fields.name: Baked Salted Almonds
fields.description: Almonds are not only extremely healthy but they are also packed with nourishing properties and are a fantastic healthy snack on the go. The interior of the nut reveals a smooth and creamy texture that is packed full of natural flavours and protein.

fields.name: Chocolate Almonds
fields.description: Experience the luscious union of smooth milk chocolate and crunchy almonds with our Milk Chocolate Almonds. These tasty morsels are not just for indulgence; they're perfect for adding a gourmet touch to your desserts, or for elevating your midday snacking.
fields.ingredients: Milk Chocolate (65%), (sugar, MILK powder, cocoa butter, cocoa mass, vegetable fat (palm SG), whey (MILK), emulsifier: sunflower lecithin (E322), glazing agents: gum arabic (E414), shellac (E904). ALMOND nut (35%). Milk chocolate contains vegetable fat in addition to cocoa butter. Cocoa solids 20% minimum.

fields.name: Salted Almond Butter
fields.description: Almonds are roasted in their natural brown skins before being ground to a smooth texture. Ingredients Roasted : Almonds (99.5%), Salt (0.5%). Gluten Free, Dairy Free, Yeast Free, Refined Sugar Free, Egg Free, Vegetarian, Vegan, Wheat FreeSoya Free, Fish Free, Shellfish Free, Sulphite Free, Celery Free, Mustard Free, Lupin Free, Mollusc Free, GMO Free, Additive Free. Delicious as a spread or use as a cooking ingredient.

fields.name: Smoked Almonds
fields.description: These Smoked Almonds are not only extremely healthy but they are also packed with nourishing properties and are a fantastic healthy snack on the go. The interior of the nut reveals a smooth and creamy texture that is packed full of natural flavours and protein.
fields.ingredients: ALMOND, rapeseed oil, salt, dextrose, rice flour, dried yeast, sugar, yeast extract powder, spice (smoked paprika, black pepper), onion powder, garlic powder, smoke flavouring, natural flavouring, citric acid.

fields.name: Almonds
fields.description: Almonds are loaded with protein and fibre and packed with vitamins, minerals and other essential nutrients. They have a creamy texture, are highly versatile and taste great raw, roasted, soaked, ground, blended or baked into your favourite foods.

fields.name: Brazil Nuts
fields.description: Organic Brazil nuts are 100% organic and an excellent source of protein and fibre whilst remaining low in carbohydrates. This makes them a great nut for a healthy balanced diet and is particularly popular on a keto diet.

fields.name: Cashew Butter
fields.description: This organic smooth cashew butter is made using 96% cashews and a dash of sunflower oil. The cashews are roasted, then ground to produce a perfectly smooth texture.
fields.ingredients: Organic Roasted Cashew Nuts (96%), Organic Sunflower Oil.

fields.name: Cashews (Pieces)
fields.description: These naturally sweet and creamy nuts are an excellent source of protein, fibre, essential minerals and many other healthy properties. They are often used in cooking both sweet and savoury meals. Soak them and add them to curries, or whizz them up to create a very 'bioavailable' nut butter. Cashew nut pieces can be scattered into stir-fries, salads, soups, curries and pretty much most savoury dishes

fields.name: Roasted Salt Pepper Cashews
fields.description: Discover the bold and sophisticated flavour of our Sea Salt & Black Pepper Cashew Nuts. These premium cashews are delicately seasoned with a perfect blend of sea salt and black pepper, creating a savoury snack that is both crunchy and irresistible. The distinct taste profile offers a satisfying balance of subtle heat from the black pepper and a touch of sea salt, perfectly complementing the natural sweetness of the cashews.
fields.ingredients: Cashew nuts (94%), Sea Salt, Spice (Black Pepper), Rice Flour, Maltodextrin, Tapioca and/or Maize Starch, Sugar, Lemon Juice Powder, Natural Flavourings.

fields.name: Roasted Salted Cashews
fields.description: These delicious nuts have been roasted and lightly salted, making them perfect for immediate snacking. Be creative and top salads, Buddha bowls and Asian-inspired cuisine for an added crunch packed full of nutrition. They are rich in fibre and contain a number of nutrients and vitamins that are essential for our body to function.

fields.name: Chestnuts
fields.description: These chestnuts are cultivated in the Ardeche region of France by some 80 organic co-operatives and growers. The Ardeche is well known for its chestnut groves that were planted as far back as the 13th century.

fields.name: Coconut Chips
fields.description: Rich in protein, coconut chips are great added to trail mix for a tasty snack or used in desserts and baking. Sprinkle on smoothie bowls for a decorative finish.

fields.name: Coconut Cream
fields.description: This deliciously rich Coconut Cream is a more concentrated, thicker version of coconut milk, made by pressing fresh organic coconut meat. This tropical ingredient is the perfect dairy free alternative to cream and can be used in both sweet and savoury Oriental, Indian and Caribbean dishes. Coconut fat content 22%.

fields.name: Coconut Drink (Rude Health)
fields.description: Coconut Drink. A refreshing alternative to milk. Pour yourself some sunshine.

fields.name: Coconut Flour
fields.description: Organic Coconut Flour is packed full of vitamins, minerals and nutrients and is a fantastic baking ingredient. This high fibre, low carbohydrate product has no gluten containing ingredients and is extremely popular among avid bakers and recipe creators. Available in bulk sizes.

fields.name: Coconut Milk Powder
fields.description: Organic coconut milk powder is made from freshly squeezed coconut milk and is suitable for vegans and vegetarians as a dairy-free milk alternative, simply add a touch of warm water and stir or add directly to hot tea and coffee.

fields.name: Coconut Milk
fields.description: Our organic coconut milk is made from the meat of mature Sri Lankan coconuts. The milk is extracted from the freshly grated flesh and blended with water to create a luxurious, velvety smooth coconut milk which is 100% natural and organic.

fields.name: Coconut Oil
fields.description: This particular oil is incredibly healthy, with many beneficial properties. And with undisputed status as the worlds best cooking and baking oil, organic virgin coconut oil will always be one of our very best-selling wholefoods.
fields.ingredients: Organic Extra Virgin Raw Coconut Oil

fields.name: Coconut Sugar
fields.description: Our organic coconut nectar sugar is subtly sweet, similar to brown sugar but with a slight hint of caramel. It is made from the blossom of the coconut plant and can be used in baking in place of sugars. Since organic coconut nectar sugar is not highly processed like other sugars, the colour, sweetness and flavour can vary.

fields.name: Toasted Coconut Chips
fields.description: Naturally sweet with no added sugar, toasted coconut chips are high in protein & fibre. Plus they are easy for you, try adding them to your baking, cooking, muesli or just eat them as a sweet & healthy snack.

fields.name: Crunchy Peanut Butter
fields.description: Our own brand, luxurious crunchy peanut butter is made with 100% nuts and no palm oil for the ultimate nut butter. Ideal for topping breakfasts, adding to smoothies or recipes and for combining with fresh apple slices for the perfect, healthy snack.

fields.name: Desiccated Coconut

fields.name: Hazelnuts (In Shell)

And cracking them might just help ward off over-indulgence too!

fields.name: Hazelnuts
fields.description: Organic Hazelnuts are one of the most popular nuts around. They are perfect for snacking on straight out the bag or adding to baking recipes for added nutrition. fields.name: Macadamia Nuts (Halves)
fields.description: Organic macadamia nut halves are crunchy, creamy and delicious. They are small size means making them a choice for adding to baking recipes such as healthy, nutty banana bread muffins for a breakfast with a difference or afternoon treat.

fields.name: Naked Salted Peanuts
fields.description: Roasted and salted peanuts have been lightly seasoned and roasted to enhance the natural flavours and goodness of a nutrient-rich snack. Not only are they a protein-packed snack and a firm favourite with those with a healthy and active lifestyle.

fields.name: Organic Cooked and Peeled Chestnuts

fields.name: Pale Skin Peanuts

fields.name: Peanut Butter

fields.name: Roasted Salted Peanuts

fields.name: Pecans (In Shell)
fields.description: Pecans are soft, delicious and highly nutritious - and there's nothing like cracking your own! Use them for light snacking, combining with other nuts or seeds, baking into sweet and nutty cakes, making desserts. Pecans also work well in many savoury settings including pie making and bread baking.

fields.name: Pecans
fields.description: Raw organic pecan nut halves are softer than other nuts and have a slightly sweet flavour than lends itself well to sweet baking. Add to homemade granola bars along with cranberries and pumpkin seeds for a nutritious treat that is packed full of goodness!

fields.name: Pine Nuts
fields.description: Frequently added to meat, fish, salads and vegetable dishes or baked into bread. In Italian, they are called pinole and are an essential component of Italian pesto sauce.

fields.name: Pistachio Nuts
fields.description: These pistachio nuts are raw, shelled and unsalted, any saltiness in flavour is completely natural. They are partially green in colour and a fantastic healthy snack.

fields.name: Raw Macadamia Nuts
fields.description: Whole, raw macadamia nuts are a highly nutritious snack suitable for any time of day. High in protein and packed full of fibre, these nuts are a great option to enhance your daily nutrient intake.

fields.name: Redskin Peanuts
fields.description: These peanuts are not just a treat for your taste buds but a versatile ingredient that can transform any dish. With their deep, earthy tones and a hint of sweetness, our Redskin Peanuts are perfectly balanced to offer a taste sensation that's both indulgent and comforting.

fields.name: Roasted Peanuts (In Shell)
fields.description: These very special peanuts have been roasted in their shell. The result is a lightly smoked, crisp and deeply satisfying nut that is kept in its shell for freshness. Simply break open and enjoy!

fields.name: Salt and Vinegar Peanuts

fields.description: Whole cashew nuts are a great healthy snack packed full of nutrients. They can be enjoyed as they are or roasted for extra flavour. Cashew nuts are great for making desserts and pasta sauce too.

fields.name: Oat Bran
fields.description: Organic oat bran is a rich source of soluble fibre and great for gut health. It is 100% organic and can be enjoyed as a high-fibre hot porridge or added to baking.

fields.name: Avocado Oil (Clearspring)

These three reasons make avocado oil a very healthy alternative to other cooking oils you may currently be using. Certainly unhealthy heat processed oils like cottonseed, corn, soy or canola oil, but also healthy oils like olive oil, due to its far higher smoke point. The fact that it tastes great too makes it even better.

fields.name: Flax Oil (Clearspring)

fields.name: Toasted Sesame Oil (Clearspring)
fields.description: The rich nutty aroma and flavour of Clearspring Organic Toasted Sesame Oil gives an authentic oriental taste to food.

fields.name: Sunflower Oil (Clearspring)
fields.description: Organic Sunflower Oil, with its golden yellow colour and distinct, nutty flavour, is a popular general-purpose oil.

fields.name: Onion Powder
fields.description: Onion powder is one of the world's best ingredients, it is great for frying, baking and all kinds of hot cooking. It's a key flavour in a number of cuisines across the world including Mexican, and Indian. The powder works with practically any other vegetable dish and a great number of spices and virtually all herbs too.

fields.name: Organic Sprouting Mix

This delicately flavoured sedanini makes a nourishing and satisfying meal and can be enjoyed hot with your favourite sauce or cold in summer salads. A genuine alternative to durum wheat pasta, not just for those avoiding gluten but for all to enjoy. Produced in a dedicated gluten and nut free facility which only uses renewable energy

fields.name: Wholegrain Fusili Pasta

fields.name: Quinoa Pasta (Gluten-Free)

fields.name: Spinach Tagliatelle

fields.name: Tricolore Penne Pasta

fields.name: Risotto Rice

fields.name: Flax Linseeds

fields.name: Hemp Seeds

fields.name: Peeled Sunflower Seeds

fields.description: One of the most essential spices around the world, black peppercorns are used in a various amount of cuisines, because of its incredible versatility.

fields.name: Cardamom Pods
fields.description: Green cardamom pods originate from the plant native to South India and are most popularly used to create authentic tasting Indian and Middle Eastern cuisine. They offer a fragrant, complex flavour that adds a punch to curries and is a fantastic spice used in baking.

fields.name: Cardamom Powder
fields.description: This pleasing green powder is yielded from the seeds of the famous green cardamom pod. It smells divine, looks beautiful, and presents a wealth of opportunities to you in the kitchen.

fields.name: Chilli Flakes
fields.description: Their vibrant colour and rich flavour go beyond mere heat, offering a smoky essence with a fruity hint that enhances any meal. Perfect for deepening the flavours of pizzas, pasta, stir-fries, or even for adding a spicy touch to oils and dressings, our chilli flakes are deliciously versatile.

fields.name: Chilli Powder
fields.description: Our chilli powder ranges from being orange to deep red with a pungent and characteristic taste. It adds a kick to dishes such as chilli con carne and curries.

fields.name: Cinnamon Powder
fields.description: Ground Cinnamon is a spice with a truly distinctive flavour. It has naturally sweet undertones and pairs well with sweet treats, homemade baking or sprinkled on hot drinks and porridge.

fields.name: Cloves
fields.description: This unmistakable, heart-warming spice is a must-have ingredient - especially if you like curries, rice dishes and traditional Indian cuisine. Brew these superior 100% organic cloves as a tea or infuse their magical flavour into stews, broths and soups.

fields.name: Coarse Black Pepper
fields.description: One of the most recognised flavours in the world the coarse black pepper is known for its robust texture and it is perfect to sprinkle on steaks, burgers, and chips.

fields.name: Cumin Seeds
fields.description: Cumin seeds shine in savoury dishes and lend themselves well to spice blends such as garam masala and taco seasoning, making them a staple in global cuisines from Indian to Mexican. Beyond their culinary uses, cumin seeds are also reputed for their health benefits, including aiding digestion and boosting immunity.

fields.name: Crystallised Ginger Sticks
fields.description: This natural standalone confectionery is not only great on its own, but heavenly when dipped in homemade chocolate, or blended with other fruits, nuts and sweet-supportive spices.

fields.name: Fenugreek Leaves
fields.description: The leaf is a popular leaf used in the Indian cuisine, they are added to dishes such as curries, dahls, dips, and methis. You can also use the leaves to garnish soups, pitta/flatbread, and many other delicious recipes.

fields.name: Garlic Powder
fields.description: Dried garlic is much more efficient, more concentrated, longer-lasting and easier to use than fresh garlic cloves. Add to recipes in the same way as you would garlic cloves.

fields.name: Ginger Dry Cut Root
fields.description: Dried ginger root cut is a fantastic cupboard essential ingredient for adding to various recipes in either sweet or savoury varieties. Ginger is particularly popular in Indian and Oriental cuisine.

fields.name: Ground Black Pepper
fields.description: Top-quality 100% organic ground black pepper, perfect for sprinkling on or into all your most cherished recipes. This classic foodstuff is super-handy for mixing with other herbs and spices, as well as making classic curry blends from across the continents.

fields.name: Ground Cumin
fields.description: Use ground cumin to create authentic curry powders, pastes and blends from all over the world. Bake beautiful bread, aromatic vegetable dishes, a soothing natural tea or two and pickles, chutneys and preserves of the very highest order. Ground cumin (also known as Jeera Powder) is also essential for making lots of Asian, Middle Eastern, North African, Mediterranean and Mexican cuisine.

fields.name: Ground Curry
fields.description: Organic Medium Curry Powder is a powerhouse of flavour! It is a classic blend of organically grown aromatic herbs and spices including coriander, turmeric, cumin, mustard, cayenne pepper, garlic, black pepper, salt, ginger and bay leaves - perfect for Indian cuisine.
fields.ingredients: Coriander, Turmeric, Cumin, MUSTARD, Cayenne, Garlic, Black Pepper, Salt, Ginger and Bay Leaves

fields.name: Ground Ginger
fields.description: Perfect for regular sweet baking and savoury cooking for several cuisines like Far Eastern, Middle Eastern, Pacific, and Indian European. It's much more efficient, concentrated, longer-lasting and easier to use than fresh ginger - and retains its matchless spicy flavour when dried.

fields.name: Habanero Chilli Flakes
fields.description: These convenient and incredibly easy-to-use chilli flakes make them an essential addition for home cooks seeking to spice up their dishes. From mouthwatering spicy tacos and flavorful habanero hot sauce, to hearty chilli con carne and zesty guacamole, these habanero chilli flakes add an irresistible spicy kick to any culinary creation.

fields.name: Himalayan Salt
fields.description: Himalayan Salt is not only great for adding to your foods, but it is also a fantastic replacement for bath salts. When this salt is used in the bath, it is great for relieving muscle and joint pain and releasing toxins from the body.

fields.name: Mixed Peppercorns
fields.description: Peppercorns are a must-have wholefood we all love to use daily. So why not make the priceless impact of this spice even more brilliant? This dynamic mix of peppercorns will give your recipes a broader peppery hit than they have ever had, and look fantastic ground freshly atop any recipe.
fields.ingredients: Peppercorns - Black, Pink, Pimento, White & Green

fields.name: Mulled Wine Spice Blend
fields.description: Discover the enchanting aroma and distinctive taste of our Mulled Wine Spice, a must-have for your festive gatherings. This meticulously crafted blend combines the warming flavours of cinnamon, cloves, nutmeg, and allspice infusing your wine with a rich and inviting essence that epitomises the spirit of the holiday season.
fields.ingredients: Cassia Bark, Orange Peel, Lemon Peel, Crushed Allspice, Nutmeg & Cloves

fields.name: Nutmeg Powder
fields.description: Ground nutmeg has a warm, subtle spice with nutty undertones and is perfect for both sweet and savoury baking and cooking. Nutmeg comes from the dark-leaved evergreen tree known as Myristica fragrans. It is a spice made by grinding the seeds of the tree into a powder form and is used as a popular spice around the world.

fields.name: Nutmeg
fields.description: Nutmeg is a must-have ingredient for those who love to bake. Use it to make heaps of classic cakes, desserts, sweet treats and snacks. But these precious whole nutmegs are also great for savoury dishes, propping up breads, curries, stews and dynamic sauces from across the UK, Europe, India, North Africa and beyond.

fields.name: Pink Peppercorn
fields.description: Pink peppercorns are visually striking and a great addition to any kitchen cupboard. Not only will they make your cooking visually striking, but their flavour will also help recipes really sing to your taste buds.

fields.name: Cinnamon Sticks
fields.description: Ceylon cinnamon sticks, also known as Ceylon cinnamon quills, can provide a delicate spice infusion to Autumnal or festive recipes. These wonderfully aromatic cinnamon sticks are yielded from Ceylon plants native to Sri Lanka - and are distinctly more nutritious and tastier than its cousin Cassia.

fields.name: Smoked Paprika
fields.description: Smoked Paprika is amazing, its versatility makes it a must-have for your spice rack. You can add fantastic flavour and colour to a number of dishes by simply adding this spice to them.

fields.name: Star Anise
fields.description: Star anise is the fruit of a plant shaped like a star, or a flower. Despite the similar name, star anise and aniseed are from two completely different plants but with the same flavour compound known as anethole. Aniseed has an almost potent flavour often used in liquor, however, star anise has a more intense liquorice flavour and is a key ingredient in five spice.

fields.name: Sweet Paprika
fields.description: This is sweet, mild paprika. Whether you use a little or a lot, this paprika will bestow your dishes with both depth and distinctiveness. Perfect for making classic cuisine from any continent - and creating novel new recipes too.

fields.name: Tikka Masala Spice Blend
fields.description: Originally from India, this spice mix is a british classic takeaway which is a favourite all across the UK. It is a great to add a number of different of recipes like salads, sandwiches and kebabs.
fields.ingredients: coriander, turmeric, salt, MUSTARD powder, cumin, garlic powder, ginger, chilli powder, paprika, citric acid, cardamom, turmeric extract, sunflower oil.

fields.name: Turmeric Powder
fields.description: Turmeric is widely used in Indian curries for its wonderful earthy flavour. It can easily adapt to a wide variety of sweet and savoury recipes from Cinnamon and Turmeric lattes to coconut turmeric curries - it provides an unmistakable colour and flavour to any dish.

fields.name: White Ground Pepper
fields.description: Ground white pepper, ready for sprinkling on or into all your most cherished recipes. This top-notch product is super-handy for mixing with other herbs and spices, as well as making classic curry blends from across the continents. Extremely well matched to mashed potatoes, mushrooms, onions, fried vegetables and classic European soups and stews.

fields.name: Zaatar Spice Blend
fields.description: A blended mixture of selected spices, popular in the Middle East. This blend is made from toasted sesame seeds, thyme, sumac and salt, our zaatar spice blend is a great addition to the spice pantry.
fields.ingredients: Toasted SESAME Seeds, Thyme, Sumac, Salt

fields.name: Split Chickpeas (Chana Dal)
fields.description: The name Chana Dal comes from Chana, being the Indian name for chickpea, and Dal means that a pulse has been split in half. The best thing about the Chana Dal is that it is quickly cooked and can be easily manipulated into a paste or just left by itself.

fields.name: Yellow Split Peas
fields.description: Closely related to the lentil, these Yellow Split Peas are perfect to use when thickening soups and stews. And they can also be used as a substitute for chickpeas in making hummus and adding to curries like Dahls.

fields.name: Sushi Rice
fields.description: Clearsprings Organic Sushi Rice is ideal for creating delicious, perfectly cooked rice that can be used in Japans most celebrated dish, sushi.

fields.name: Tahini
fields.description: Our Organic Dark Roasted Tahini is made from 100% unshelled organic sesame seeds and has a creamy, smooth consistency making it easy to drizzle on your fave meals.

fields.name: White Basmati Rice
fields.description: Basmati rice is a unique grain, it expands more than twice its length when it's cooking, also unlike other rice, it expands lengthways. Having both white and brown versions, the basmati rice both give us vital nutrients which we need to live, with brown basmati rice has more fibre and vitamins in but the white version is easier to digest.

fields.name: Wild Rice
fields.description: Organic Wild Rice is a special type of rice that is very chewy and tasty when boiled. It contains several vital nutrients and is higher in protein than your regular rice. But it is also very versatile, tasty and well-suited to countless classic recipes enjoyed across the UK and Europe.

fields.name: Vegan Violife Cheese Slices
fields.description: The classic flavour that gives you your cheesy hit in a variety of recipes, in a humble sandwich or grilled for ultimate comfort food. Add to a plate some grapes, crackers and chutney alongside this vegan cheese will blow you away with its flavour.
fields.ingredients: Water, Coconut oil (23%), Modified Starch*, Starch, Sea salt, Flavourings, Olive extract, Colour: B-Carotene, Vitamin B12. *Not to be confused with GMO (Genetically Modified) ingredients.

fields.name: Vegan Violife Cream Cheese
fields.description: Your favourite Vegan treat in a spreadable, creamy variety. It speaks for itself.
fields.ingredients: Water, Coconut Oil (23%), Starch, Sea Salt, Acidity Regulator: Glucono-Delta-Lactone, Flavourings, Olive Extract, Vitamin B12.

fields.name: Smoked Tofu (Taifun)
fields.description: A classic version of Smoked Tofu. Enjoy cold on bread or in a salad. Excellent pan-fried with vegetable dishes, rice, potatoes or pasta.
fields.ingredients: Tofu 93% (SOYA BEANS, water, coagulating agents: magnesium chloride, calcium sulfate), SOYA sauce* (water, SOYA BEANS, wheat, sea salt), beech wood smoke. organic

fields.name: Firm Tofu (Taifun)
fields.description: This traditional basic tofu is full of high-quality vegetable protein and extremely versatile. Tangy, spicy, sweet or sour this natural tofu can be prepared to take on any desired taste. Due to its firm texture, it is particularly suitable for frying.
fields.ingredients: Water, SOYA BEANS* 55%, coagulating agents: magnesium chloride, calcium sulfate. organic
